Euro Disney's creditor banks gave the green light  Thursday to a restructuring programme for the troubled theme park, agreeing to  underwrite 51 percent of a billion-dollar investment package, two leading  banks said.
The Banque Nationale de Paris (BNP), together with Indosuez the lead  institutions of the 61 creditor banks, said that "with the exception of a few  banks, all the establishments have agreed to guarantee the increase in  capital, which should be in made available in June or July."
The programme, providing six billion francs (1.06 billion dollars) of new  funding, was signed March 14 by the banks, Euro Disney and its parent  organisation, the Walt Disney Company, which will fund the remaining 49  percent of the package.
